   If the method throws an exception, then you can test for that.

   Example:

   public void someMethod(String imput) throws SomeException
   {
        if(input.equals(badInput)
             throw new SomeException();

        else
          &quot; lif is good&quot;
   }


  You then test it with &quot;good&quot; input and &quot;bad&quot; input on your testcase.

  void testGood()
  {  
     try{
      obj.someMethod(&quot;Good Input&quot;);
      }
      catch(SomeException se)
      {
          fail(&quot;Oops.. failed on good input&quot;);
      }
  }

  void testBar()
  {  
     try{
      obj.someMethod(&quot;Good Input&quot;);
       fail(&quot;Oops.. Should have thrown an exception&quot;);
      }
      catch(SomeException se)
      {
         // test passed.
      }
  }


  Hope this helps.

